<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 4:59PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Garfield, south central McCone and northwestern Prairie Counties
through 600 PM MDT...
At 457 PM MDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm 12 miles northeast of Cohagen, or 23 miles east of
Jordan, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Crow Rock.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
